XSUD software is designed for legal proceedings record keeping. The service is applied for systematization of information on legal proceedings, notifications on important events, automation of reports making and lawyers’ team work management. 

The main features of XSUD Software are:
- Creation of common information space for legal department operation; 
- Record keeping on legal proceedings, claims, inspections, enforcement proceedings and contracts; 
- Automated downloading of information on legal proceedings from kad.arbitr.ru portal; 
- Adjustment of personal calendar for each lawyer with automatic notifications about forthcoming events; 
- Making reports and statements on legal proceedings; 
- Setting and control of instructions execution; 
- Safety assurance and data access control.

Effects of XSUD Software implementation are: 
- Increase of information availability for each lawyer/Advanced information availability for each lawyer; 
- Reduction of monthly labor costs for reports making; 
- Reduction of the risks of important information loss; 
- Increase of to each lawyer’s operation efficiency and efficiency of legal department operation as a whole.

OSA - Consultation Platform for Attorneys by Attorneys

OSA was developed in cooperation with Belgian Attorneys in order to enable Attorneys and Solicitors to offer online legal services through a simple and accessible user interface. The website is the result of extensive research and analysis aimed at finding a harmonious balance between ethics rules and economic laws at European level.

Thanks to its intuitive features, OSA provides the following advantages for the Attorneys:

·      No registration fees;
·      Their online professional page;
·      Their listing in the OSA directory;
·      The possibility to offer legal services trough Skype or/and emails;
·      The order cancellation option;
·      The automation of the withdrawal process; 
·      The possibility to update their profile at any time;
·      The possibility to publish legal notes on the website and social networks; and
·      Pre-paid consultations.

OSA is currently available in Belgium, France and Luxembourg.

